sentences: Medina Danielle Oona Valbak (born Andrea Fuentealba Valbak; 30 November 1982), known as Medina (Danish: [me̝ˈtiːnæ]; Spanish: [meˈðina]), was born in Denmark, and is a Danish singer and songwriter.
At the 2010 Danish Music Awards, she won female artist of the year, Album of the year, and Songwriter of the year.
She released her first two single's in Denmark titled "Flå" ("Rip") and "Et Øjeblik" ("One Moment") in 2007.

sentences: She rose to fame primarily within several countries in Western Europe in 2008 with the release of "Kun for mig" (which was later released in English as "You and I"), the lead single off her second album, Velkommen til Medina (Welcome to Medina).

sentences: 2011–2012: For Altid and Forever =
In 2011 her Danish studio album For Altid was released, including the single's "Synd for Dig", "For Altid", "Kl. 10", "12 Dage", "Lyser i Morke", and "Har du Glemt".
It was followed up in 2012 by the English version of the same name, titled Forever.

section: == Career == | === 2013–2018: Hiatus, small projects, and return with We Survive and Grim ===

sentences: From 2013 to 2015 Medina went on a short hiatus between 2012–14, later embarking on smaller projects, including the release of an urban inspired EP, and a live album, which are both primarily in Danish.

She changed her name in 2005 to Medina Danielle Oona Valbak after visiting a numerologist.
In 2007 she was in a relationship with Samir Soud.
Shortly after that she had a relationship with dancer Mathias Arvedsen until 2011.
From 2012 to 2014 she dated and lived with Danish singer Christopher, who is 9 years younger.
As of 2014 she was in a relationship with model Mikkel Gregers Jensen; they broke up in 2015.
As of 2014 she was in a relationship with model Mikkel Gregers Jensen; they broke up in 2015.
Medina was confirmed in August 2020 to be expecting her first child with husband Malo Chapsal.
She posted a story on her Instagram profile in December 2021 which said: "Sick how there are no limits to how much you can lie and misinform people!!!!".

In the latter half of 2020 Medina would go onto release several new singles, mostly in Danish, including several Danish covers from the new season of "Toppen Af Poppen" (Danish TV Show), where she makes a return for the new season of the show.
